              highlights: [
                "ADR-20260312-03: Separate logical and physical structure (karasu's core)",
                "ADR-20260312-04: CSS-inspired styling system",
                "ADR-20260317-01: Two-layer rendering with drill-down",
                "ADR-20260317-02: FileSystemProvider + OPFS",
                "ADR-20260324-01: Prefer manual QA over E2E",
                "feat!: rename person to user with role and human/ai tags (#2)",
                "feat: organization diagram (organization/team/member) (#39)",
              ],
            },
            {
              name: "April",
              subtitle: "Expansion — a burst of features and design decisions",
              narrative:
                "The peak of development — <strong>544 commits and 109 ADRs in one month</strong>. Multi-file imports with wildcard resolution, cross-system references and Ghost Systems, and cyclic-dependency detection landed. The <strong>Chat UI (BYOK AI)</strong> was built across Phases 1–3. The CLI gained <code>translate</code>/<code>diff</code>/<code>apply</code> and a formatter. The layout engine was refined with barycenter ordering, orthogonal routing, and skip-layer channels, and the <strong>client kind shipped across Phases 1–7</strong>. Legend syntax, the i18n rollout, draw.io export, and the diff viewer all arrived. On the infrastructure side: the <strong>ADR knowledge graph</strong>, the feature-toggle policy, Cloudflare Pages deploy, and the VS Code Phase 3 Webview + ExTester harness.",
